794—5. Translate, ‘do you suppose it makes little difference whether all your acts are sincere and natural, or all premeditated?'

Davos means that Mysis would certainly have betrayed herself had she attempted to act a part3 the only chance was to keep her in the dark, so that she could speak and act naturally.
